-- OfficeMax names CEO
-- 
-- Wed Oct 13, 2010 7:09pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/10/13/us-officemax-idUSTRE69C6MB20101013

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. office supplies retailer OfficeMax Inc OMX.N said it named Ravi Saligram as its president and chief executive officer, effective November 8. 

 Saligram, 54, replaces Sam Duncan, who has already announced his plans to retire. Duncan, 57, will continue to work for OfficeMax as a special advisor until the end of February next year. Saligram most recently served as president of Aramark International, a unit of contract food service provider Aramark Corp. (Reporting by  Dhanya Skariachan ; Editing by Phil Berlowitz)